Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @Potatoes{450%grams} lengthways into 1cm slices, then chop into 1cm
wide chips (no need to peel).

Pop the chips onto a large #baking tray{}. Sprinkle with the @Dried Rosemary{1%sachet}. Drizzle with oil, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to
coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, bake on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn
halfway through.

Meanwhile, halve, peel and thinly slice the @Onion{1}.

Grate the @Red Leicester{30%grams}.

In a #medium bowl{}, add a drizzle of @olive oil{} and season with @salt{}
and @pepper{}. Set your dressing aside.

Melt the @Butter{20%grams} in a large #saucepan{} on medium heat.

Once hot, add the onion, season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and fry, stirring
occasionally until golden, ~{10-12%minutes}.

Meanwhile, in a #large bowl{}, combine the @Onion Marmalade{30%grams} and
@British Pork and Oregano Sausage Meat{225%grams}. Season with @pepper{} and
mix together with your hands. Roll into even-sized balls, then shape into 1cm
thick square burgers, 1 per person.

> TIP: The burgers will shrink a little during cooking.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

Pop your square burgers onto a large lined baking tray.

When the oven is hot, bake on the middle shelf until cooked through,
~{12-15%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The burgers are cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, when the onions are golden, add the @Balsamic Vinegar{12%ml} and
@Sugar for the Onions{1/2%tsp} and cook until caramelised, ~{1-2%minutes} more.
Set aside.

Once the burgers are cooked, carefully place the Red Leicester on top of the
burgers and pop back into the oven until the cheese has melted, ~{2-3%minutes}.

At the same time, pop the @Sliced Burger Buns{2} into oven to warm through,
~{2-3%minutes}.

Just before serving, toss the @Baby Leaf Mix{20%grams} in the dressing.

> TIP: Don't add the leaves too early or they'll go soggy.

When everything's ready, spread the @Tomato Ketchup{2%tbsp} over the bun lids.
Top the bases with the square sausage burgers, some caramelised onion and
dressed baby leaves, then sandwich shut with the bun lids.

Serve with the rosemary chips on the side. Enjoy!